works.description: Both the Italian jewelry company Damiani and the Modena-based automotive manufacturer Maserati think of luxury as the perfect match between innovation and craftsmanship. The two Italian icons have been working together since 2009, and have lately presented the new Masterpiece key-ring and the Circle collection at the Baselworld 2011. The collection has been made to complement Maserati’s cars. The highlight of the collection, the Masterpiece key-ring is made from 18-carat white gold and is festooned with 232 blue sapphires and 66 diamonds that form the signature Maserati trident. On the back of the key-ring is the engraved Maserati signature
